{
  "page": "Needle",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:LucasDurham_Needle.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/c0/LucasDurham_Needle.jpg/350px-LucasDurham_Needle.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"274\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/c0/LucasDurham_Needle.jpg/525px-LucasDurham_Needle.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/c0/LucasDurham_Needle.jpg/700px-LucasDurham_Needle.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:LucasDurham_Needle.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a> draws Needle, by Lucas Durham © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Needle</b> is a small, slender sword owned by <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance\">Appearance</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Needle&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<dl><dd><i>See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_Needle\" title=\"Category:Images of Needle\">Images of Needle</a></i></dd></dl>\n<p>Needle is a slender<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> sword with a deep blue sheen of <a href=\"/index.php/Steel\" title=\"Steel\">steel</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and a smooth pommel.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Mikken\" title=\"Mikken\">Mikken</a>'s mark is on the blade.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Its scabbard is soft grey leather.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Needle is suitable to <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a>'s slight build and the <a href=\"/index.php/Water_dance\" title=\"Water dance\">water dance</a> style used by <a href=\"/index.php/Bravo\" title=\"Bravo\">bravos</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_Cities\" title=\"Free Cities\">Free Cities</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Needle&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Needle&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Before leaving for the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a> commissions <a href=\"/index.php/Mikken\" title=\"Mikken\">Mikken</a> to make the sword for his sister, <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a>. The girl names it Needle as an ironic reference to her hatred of needlework.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Eddard Stark</a> hires <a href=\"/index.php/Syrio_Forel\" title=\"Syrio Forel\">Syrio Forel</a>, a <a href=\"/index.php/Water_dancer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Water dancer\">water dancer</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavos</a>, to train Arya.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a> purges the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Stark\" title=\"House Stark\">House Stark</a> after <a href=\"/index.php/Arrest_of_Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Arrest of Eddard Stark\">Eddard's arrest</a>, Arya kills <a href=\"/index.php/Stableboy_at_King%27s_Landing\" title=\"Stableboy at King&#39;s Landing\">a stableboy</a> with Needle while fleeing.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Arya uses Needle against a mob gathered at the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Sept_of_Baelor\" title=\"Great Sept of Baelor\">Great Sept of Baelor</a> to witness Eddard's public confession. She drops the sword when <a href=\"/index.php/Yoren\" title=\"Yoren\">Yoren</a> interrupts and grabs her, but the <a href=\"/index.php/Wandering_crow\" title=\"Wandering crow\">wandering crow</a> returns the blade to her.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Needle&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Oozn_needlework.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/2/26/Oozn_needlework.jpg/350px-Oozn_needlework.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"191\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/2/26/Oozn_needlework.jpg/525px-Oozn_needlework.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/2/26/Oozn_needlework.jpg/700px-Oozn_needlework.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Oozn_needlework.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a> practicing her needlework, by Oozn ©</div></div></div>\n<p>While travelling northward in Yoren's company of recruits for the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Hot_Pie\" title=\"Hot Pie\">Hot Pie</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Lommy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lommy\">Lommy</a> make fun of Needle and attempt to take it from Arya, but she successfully defends herself with a wooden practice sword.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> She offers to spar with <a href=\"/index.php/Gendry\" title=\"Gendry\">Gendry</a>, she with Needle and he with <a href=\"/index.php/Praed\" title=\"Praed\">Praed</a>'s longsword, but they are interrupted by the arrival of <a href=\"/index.php/Gold_cloaks\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gold cloaks\">gold cloaks</a> who are searching for Gendry. When Arya enters a <a href=\"/index.php/Water_dancer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Water dancer\">water dancer</a>'s pose wielding Needle, <a href=\"/index.php/Broken_Nose\" title=\"Broken Nose\">Broken Nose</a> laughs at her.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Arya's fingers become calloused from long hours of practicing with Needle,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> and she always keeps the blade close at hand.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> While standing watch at the <a href=\"/index.php/Gods_Eye_town\" title=\"Gods Eye town\">Gods Eye town</a>, she uses Yoren's whetstone to hone Needle. The town comes under attack by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Amory_Lorch\" title=\"Amory Lorch\">Amory Lorch</a>, and Arya cuts off the fingers of an attacking <a href=\"/index.php/Westerman\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Westerman\">westerman</a> with Needle.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Arya loses Needle when she is captured by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">Gregor Clegane</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Mountain%27s_men\" title=\"Mountain&#39;s men\">Mountain's men</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a>;<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> Arya adds <a href=\"/index.php/Polliver\" title=\"Polliver\">Polliver</a>, the man-at-arms who took Needle, to her prayer kill list.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Practicing with a broken broomstick while at <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a>, she refers to her swordplay as needlework.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok64.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok64.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Needle&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Arya arrives at the <a href=\"/index.php/Inn_at_the_crossroads\" title=\"Inn at the crossroads\">inn at the crossroads</a> in the custody of <a href=\"/index.php/Sandor_Clegane\" title=\"Sandor Clegane\">Sandor Clegane</a>. There she spots Polliver carrying Needle, accompanied by the <a href=\"/index.php/Tickler\" title=\"Tickler\">Tickler</a>. Arya and the <a href=\"/index.php/Hound\" title=\"Hound\">Hound</a> cross these two names off her list, and Arya retrieves her sword. Arya uses Needle to kill the <a href=\"/index.php/Pimply_squire\" title=\"Pimply squire\">pimply squire</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/House_Sarsfield\" title=\"House Sarsfield\">House Sarsfield</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos74.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos74.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Needle&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Arya pats Needle's hilt for luck when she reaches the <a href=\"/index.php/House_of_Black_and_White\" title=\"House of Black and White\">House of Black and White</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavos</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> where she begins training to become a servant of the <a href=\"/index.php/Many-Faced_God\" title=\"Many-Faced God\">Many-Faced God</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> She secretly practices her swordplay, dueling with her shadow by the light of a blue candle, but is spotted by the <a href=\"/index.php/Waif\" title=\"Waif\">waif</a> one night. The <a href=\"/index.php/Kindly_man\" title=\"Kindly man\">kindly man</a> tells Arya she must up all her possessions to train, so the girl drops her belongings into the lagoon outside the temple. Arya cannot bring herself to give up Needle, however, and she instead hides the sword and sheath in a crack in the stairs leading to the House of Black and White.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Needle&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:102px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Needle,_Sword_of_Arya_Stark.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/4c/Needle%2C_Sword_of_Arya_Stark.jpg/100px-Needle%2C_Sword_of_Arya_Stark.jpg\" width=\"100\" height=\"385\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/4/4c/Needle%2C_Sword_of_Arya_Stark.jpg/150px-Needle%2C_Sword_of_Arya_Stark.jpg 1.5x, /images/4/4c/Needle%2C_Sword_of_Arya_Stark.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Needle,_Sword_of_Arya_Stark.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Depiction of Needle from the Valyrian Steel Collection</div></div></div>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Arya</b>: It's so skinny.<br /><b>Jon</b>: So are you. I had <a href=\"/index.php/Mikken\" title=\"Mikken\">Mikken</a> make this special. The <a href=\"/index.php/Bravo\" title=\"Bravo\">bravos</a> use swords like this in <a href=\"/index.php/Pentos\" title=\"Pentos\">Pentos</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Myr\" title=\"Myr\">Myr</a> and the other <a href=\"/index.php/Free_Cities\" title=\"Free Cities\">Free Cities</a>. It won't hack a man's head off, but it can poke him full of holes if you're fast enough.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Jon</b>: First lesson. Stick 'em with the pointy end.<br /><b>Arya</b>: I know which end to use.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The slender blade seemed very small and <a href=\"/index.php/Skulls_of_the_Targaryen_dragons\" title=\"Skulls of the Targaryen dragons\">the dragons</a> very big, yet somehow Arya felt better with <a href=\"/index.php/Steel\" title=\"Steel\">steel</a> in her hand.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Mountain%27s_men\" title=\"Mountain&#39;s men\">They</a> took Needle. The shame of that hurt worse than the pain, and the pain hurt a lot. <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon</a> had given her that sword. <a href=\"/index.php/Syrio\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Syrio\">Syrio</a> had taught her to use it.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>I don't need any friends, so long as I have Needle.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Needle was <a href=\"/index.php/Robb_Stark\" title=\"Robb Stark\">Robb</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Rickon_Stark\" title=\"Rickon Stark\">Rickon</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">her mother</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">her father</a>, even <a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">Sansa</a>. Needle was <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a>'s grey walls, and the laughter of its people. Needle was the summer snows, <a href=\"/index.php/Old_Nan\" title=\"Old Nan\">Old Nan</a>'s stories, the <a href=\"/index.php/Godswood_of_Winterfell\" title=\"Godswood of Winterfell\">heart tree</a> with its red leaves and scary face, the warm earthy smell of the <a href=\"/index.php/Glass_gardens\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Glass gardens\">glass gardens</a>, the sound of the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">north</a> wind rattling the shutters of her room. Needle was <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a>'s smile.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The gods wanted me to have it. Not the <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">Seven</a>, nor Him of Many Faces, but <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">her father's</a> gods, the <a href=\"/index.php/Old_gods\" title=\"Old gods\">old gods</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">north</a>. The <a href=\"/index.php/Many-Faced_God\" title=\"Many-Faced God\">Many-Faced God</a> can have the rest, she thought, but he can't have this.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Needle&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\">1.5</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\">1.6</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones-Chapter_10\" title=\"A Game of Thrones-Chapter 10\">Chapter 10</a>, Jon II.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\">2.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\">2.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/